snippet.textDisplay: 2:08 As a dancer I want to tell him so bad that it doesn't matter if you don't give off the same vibe/feeling as the original. Everyone is different when they dance, we are shaped by what we've been through and what we like. He still lacks experience. I'm not much older than him but I saw my way of dancing changing as I watched other people dance and discovered new things. If I could tell him anything in person it would be to pick things from Taemin that matches him at the moment and add his own charm and think about what the song makes him feel personally. Trying to replicate a vibe/feeling that you probably never experienced yourself yet will often result in an awkward/unnatural performance (as we could see in this clip, his body moved nice enough but he didn't know what to do with his face at all and felt awkward because he probably felt like he didn't match the vibe he's imposing on himself). In my case I've been influenced by Britney, Madonna, MJ, Aya Sato, (fx) Victoria, (SNSD) Hyoyeon, (BTS) Jimin, (BTS) J Hope and Taemin. As I watched them I slowly started to progress because I listened to different music styles and discovered more tips and tricks that helped me find out how I want to express myself. Move is obviously a sexy kind of song but it's what you make of it that changes the mood when you perform, if that makes any sense XD I hope one what I say will make sense xD I guess my message is: Be open-minded and get inspired by as much people as you can but be yourself.
